OL,3,CHistoric Grade-II listed pub reopens
OL,4,Cafter being saved by local community
OL,6,FThe work has all been led and
OL,7,Fcoordinated by the Save the Hop Pole
OL,8,Fcampaign group, who first secured the
OL,9,Fsite in 2022 - though it has been a
OL,10,Fturbulent process.
OL,12,FSpeaking as it reopened, Simon Coombe
OL,13,Fsaid: "It is one of the best days of
OL,14,Fof our lives. It has been three years
OL,15,Fof incredibly hard work by over a
OL,16,Fthousand people in this community. But
OL,17,Fthe community spirit has won through.
OL,18,FWe thought we were going to lose our
OL,19,Fpub but now we've got our pub forever."
OL,21,FWhat happened to the Hop Pole Inn?
