OL,3,CHistoric Grade-II listed pub reopens
OL,4,Cafter being saved by local community
OL,6,FThey also appealed for volunteers to
OL,7,Fhelp them redecorate the pub, which
OL,8,Fsaw people from all over muck in. A
OL,9,FSomali refugee living in Bristol even
OL,10,Fused the pub as a place to teach
OL,11,Ffellow refugees how to plaster.
OL,13,FThe new tenants - Charlie Rawlings and
OL,14,FHannah Randall - were then selected by
OL,15,Fthe team and an opening date was
OL,16,Fselected.
OL,18,FFinally, almost three years after the
OL,19,Fcommunity first bought the pub, it has
OL,20,Fheld its official reopening.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
