OL,3,CHistoric Grade-II listed pub reopens
OL,4,Cafter being saved by local community
OL,6,FTim Tuckey, another member of the Save
OL,7,FThe Hop Pole campaign group, said he
OL,8,Fwas responsible for coordinating 130
OL,9,Fvolunteers to make the pub happen.
OL,11,FHe said: "From young Seb and Arthur,
OL,12,Fwho are doing their Bronze and Silver
OL,13,FDuke of Edinburgh awards, to people in
OL,14,Ftheir seventies who have given up
OL,15,Fhundreds of hours of their time.
OL,17,F"They have turned what three years ago
OL,18,Fwas just a dream, to the reality of
OL,19,Fthe Hop Pole Inn today."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
